        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 10:21PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1021 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Midland, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tarzan, Courtney, Midland, Cotton Flat, Greenwood, Stanton, Lenorah,
Midland Airpark, Stanton Municipal Aiport, Skywest Airport, and
Midland International Air and Space Port.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 129 and 162.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
